7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Descript and Elai share a solid foundation of core features including Auto Captions, Templates, Voice Over. Where Descript pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Screen Recording, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Elai uniquely offers Text To Video and Avatar Talking Head and Stock Footage and Api Access, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Descript holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Elai scores 6/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Elai comes in at a lower starting price of $23/mo, while Descript begins at $24/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Descript's free tier and Elai's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
