b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Descript is best suited for podcasters and YouTubers, text based video editing, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Elai, meanwhile, shines for marketing teams, training video creation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Descript describes itself as \"Edit video as easily as editing a document.\" Elai, established in 2021, positions itself as \"Create AI videos from text with digital avatars.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Descript** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 6.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Elai is a poor choice — far from it. Elai excels in its own right, particularly for marketing teams and training video creation.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value revolutionary text-based editing, go with Descript. If clone your own avatar matters more to you, Elai is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
